cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses the problem of feedback error in wireless communication, which is a key issue in the field of networked systems and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a new method for acknowledging packet delivery in retransmission protocols, which involves analyzing the reliability of the feedback channel. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the proposed method involves providing the scheduler of the wireless channel with additional parameters to configure ultra-reliable communication, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
